SIMPLE: naught
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Naught
<hw>Naught</hw> <pr>(n⟦add⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>naught</ets>, <ets>nought</ets>, <ets>naht</ets>,
<ets>nawiht</ets>, AS. <ets>n⟦amac⟧wiht</ets>, <ets>n⟦amac⟧uht</ets>,
<ets>n⟦amac⟧ht</ets>; <ets>ne</ets> not + <ets>⟦amac⟧</ets> ever +
<ets>wiht</ets> thing, whit; hence, not ever a whit. See <er>No</er>,
<pos>adv.</pos> <er>Whit</er>, and cf. <er>Aught</er>,
<er>Not</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Nothing.</def> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>nought</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Doth Job fear God for <qex>naught</qex>?</q> <rj><qau>Job i.
9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The arithmetical character 0; a cipher. See
<er>Cipher</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To set at naught</b></col>, <cd>to treat as of no
account; to disregard; to despise; to defy; to treat with ignominy.</cd>
⟦ldquo⟧Ye have <xex>set at naught</xex> all my counsel.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Prov. i. 25.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Naught</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Naught
<hw>Naught</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In no degree; not at all.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To wealth or sovereign power he <qex>naught</qex> applied.</q>
<rj><qau>Fairfax.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Naught</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Naught
<hw>Naught</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of no value or account;
worthless; bad; useless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is <qex>naught</qex>, it is <qex>naught</qex>, saith the
buyer.</q> <rj><qau>Prov. xx. 14.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Go, get you to your house; begone, away!⟦br⟧
All will be <qex>naught</qex> else.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Things <qex>naught</qex> and things indifferent.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, vile; base; naughty.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No man can be stark <qex>naught</qex> at once.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Naughtily</ent>⟦br⟧
